column5: It has been reported to me that at Nestor Falls the lake is down 3'? I'm wondering how hard it is to launch at the goverment dock or at Vic and Dot's. It would seem to be very difficult if this is true. How has fishing been out by Hay Ialand or at White Fish Bay? Just two weeks to wait.

O/F We put in at the Govt dock and it was fine but that was in June and the lake was definitely down then but I would guess closer to 2'. You could probably go to witchbay.com and see their report. Good Luck.
We launched out of Morson Marina in late July, no problem. Water level is same now as it was then.
Both launches are good ,just wear sandals because your feet may get wet at Vic and Dots when you want to winch your boat up.
